    "summary": "4 epistemology edits made to Essay4 draft — two expert reviews complete",
    "content": "Four more edits made to the draft based on epistemology-expert's review:\n\n1. \"summarized from phenomena\" → \"derived from phenomena\" (总结 = epistemic extraction, not condensation)\n2. \"a property we have inductively generalized\" → \"an inductively derived property\" (avoids tautology)\n3. \"rightness issues in ritual conduct\" → \"from rightness one practices ritual conduct\" (行 = active; fixed in both occurrences)\n4. Standardized all 发乎于心 as \"arises from the heart\" (was inconsistently \"from within me\" vs \"from within the heart\")\n\nDeclined one suggestion: adding \"a status arrived at through induction rather than given a priori\" to TN3 -- existing phrasing already covers the point without importing Kantian terminology.\n\nThe draft has now been reviewed and revised by both phenomenology-expert and epistemology-expert. \n\nFile: `/Users/el/Dropbox/10.Kernel/11.Vault/Tower/L. Legenravend/49 Workspace/Translator/Draft/Essay4-DaoDeRenYiLi.md`"
  }
}
